  <h1>Creating Wikis in Markdown</h1>
  <p>* For a quick intro, checkout this <a href="https://github.com/adam-p/markdown-here/wiki/Markdown-Cheatsheet">Markdown</a> cheat sheet.</p>
  <h4>Some simple notations you can use to style your wikis:
    <ul>
      <li># will be rendered as a header. The number of hashes denotes the number of the h tag.
        <ul>
          <li># - h1</li>
          <li>## - h2</li>
          <li>...</li>
          <li>###### - h6</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>You can denote code blocks by using a pair of triple backticks (above the tab key). ``` ...code block...```</li>
      <li>Use _x_ for underline, __x__ for bold, ==x== for highlights, and *x* for italics.</li>
      <li>You can link footnotes using [^1] syntax.
        <ul>
          <li>Mark this sentence with a footnote.[^4]</li>
          <li>...</li>
          <li>[^4]: Denotes the corresponding footnote.</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </h4>
